# Page Patterns

## `page.tsx`

- Presentation only — Tailwind layout and JSX, no inline logic
- `const { data, methods } = useHooks();` at the top
- `const LoginPage = () => { ... }; export default LoginPage;`
- Prefer Server Component when static; add `"use client"` when using `useHooks()` directly
- Alternative: Server `page.tsx` + colocated client child (e.g. `login-view.tsx`)

## `hooks.ts`

- Required for interactive pages; exports `useHooks` (per-folder convention)
- `"use client"` when using state/effects/browser APIs
- Return exactly `{ data, methods }` — process API responses before exposing

## Output order

`types.ts` (if needed) → `hooks.ts` → `page.tsx`
